@startuml activity_resolver_detail_design

title ActivityResolver Detail Design

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left
skinparam wrapWidth 220

rectangle "RawActivityDiagram\n- name: Option<String>\n- statements: Vec<RawActivityStmt>" as raw_doc
rectangle "ActivityDiagram\n- name: Option<String>\n- statements: Vec<ActivityStmt>" as logic_doc
rectangle "ActivityResolverError\n- UnexpectedEndOfInput\n- UnexpectedStatement\n- UnsupportedStatement" as resolver_error

package "ActivityResolver" {
  rectangle "cursor: usize" as cursor

  rectangle "resolve(document)" as resolve
  rectangle "visit_block_until(statements, terminator)" as visit_block
  rectangle "visit_statement(statements)" as visit_stmt
  rectangle "visit_loop_body_until(statements, terminator)" as visit_loop

  rectangle "visit_if(statements, condition, then_label)" as visit_if
  rectangle "visit_while(statements, condition, continue_label)" as visit_while
  rectangle "visit_repeat_while(statements)" as visit_repeat

  rectangle "consume_endif(statements)" as consume_endif
  rectangle "consume_endwhile_label(statements)" as consume_endwhile
  rectangle "consume_repeat_while_data(statements)" as consume_repeat

  rectangle "peek_statement(statements)" as peek_stmt
  rectangle "next_statement(statements)" as next_stmt
  rectangle "resolve_control_kind(kind)" as resolve_control
}

raw_doc --> resolve : input
resolve --> cursor : reset to 0
resolve --> visit_block : terminator = false
visit_block --> peek_stmt : stop when terminator matches
visit_block --> visit_stmt : resolve each non-terminator stmt
visit_stmt --> next_stmt : consume current raw stmt
visit_stmt --> resolve_control : map RawControlKind

visit_stmt --> visit_if : RawActivityStmt::IfStart
visit_stmt --> visit_while : RawActivityStmt::WhileStart
visit_stmt --> visit_repeat : RawActivityStmt::RepeatStart

visit_if --> visit_block : then body until Else/EndIf
visit_if --> visit_block : else body until EndIf
visit_if --> consume_endif

visit_while --> visit_loop : body until EndWhile
visit_while --> consume_endwhile

visit_repeat --> visit_loop : body until RepeatWhile
visit_repeat --> consume_repeat

visit_loop --> peek_stmt : inspect next stmt
visit_loop --> visit_stmt : non-Backward stmt
resolve --> logic_doc : build ActivityDiagram
resolve ..> resolver_error : propagate errors
visit_block ..> resolver_error
visit_stmt ..> resolver_error
visit_if ..> resolver_error
visit_while ..> resolver_error
visit_repeat ..> resolver_error
consume_endif ..> resolver_error
consume_endwhile ..> resolver_error
consume_repeat ..> resolver_error

note right of resolve
Single-pass recursive descent.

1. Reset cursor.
2. Resolve the whole document through visit_block_until.
3. Return ActivityDiagram with preserved document name.
end note

note right of visit_stmt
Raw statement dispatch:

- Title -> ActivityStmt::Title
- Arrow | Start -> skipped in logic AST
- Action -> ActivityStmt::Action
- Stop -> Control(kind = Stop)
- Control -> Control(kind mapped from parser enum)
- IfStart -> visit_if(...)
- WhileStart -> visit_while(...)
- RepeatStart -> visit_repeat_while(...)

Errors:

- Else / EndIf / EndWhile / RepeatWhile / Backward
  at statement position -> UnexpectedStatement
- Fork* / Swimlane -> UnsupportedStatement
end note

note right of visit_loop
Loop-body special rule:

- Backward is not emitted as a sequential ActivityStmt.
- It is captured as BackwardNode on the loop back-edge.
- If multiple backward statements appear, the last one wins.
- The function advances cursor directly after consuming Backward.
end note

note bottom of consume_endif
Structured terminator helpers enforce block boundaries.
If the next raw stmt is missing or of the wrong kind,
the resolver returns a precise structural error.
end note

note bottom of logic_doc
Semantic output keeps only structured control-flow nodes:

- Title
- Action
- If
- While
- RepeatWhile
- Control

Arrow and Start remain parser-level syntax markers
and are intentionally dropped during resolution.
end note

@enduml
